<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "S5JB0A4306005" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Rear Brake Shoe On-Vehicle Check
</title>
<ptxt>
Inspection should be carried out on the following points after brake pedal travel (pedal to silencer clearance) check as described on 
<intxref refid = "S5JB0A4106001">Excessive Pedal Travel Check</intxref>
, even when it is more than specification.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Amount of brake shoe wear can be checked as follows.
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Hoist vehicle.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove rubber plug (1) from brake back plate.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Through hole of back plate, visually check for thickness of brake shoe lining (2). If lining thickness less than specified wear limit, replace with new brake shoes.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Lining thickness &#8220;a&#8221;
</title>
<ptxt>
Service limit: 1.0 mm (0.04 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5JB0A430005.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.745mm" ver = "01" gw = "186" gh = "124"/>
